# Example: CLAUDE.md (Claude Code)

# Place this file at `CLAUDE.md` in your project root.

## Operating System

This project uses the Agentic Kernel framework for structured development.
Read `.agents/SYSTEM_CORE.md` before starting any task.

## Mandatory Workflow

For every task:
1. **Plan first** — Create or update `PLAN.md` using `.agents/skills/01_mission_synthesis/02_strategic_decomposition.md`
2. **Test first** — Write failing tests before implementation per `.agents/skills/02_execution_engine/05_incremental_proof_cycles.md`
3. **Commit atomically** — One task = one commit per `.agents/skills/02_execution_engine/04_state_checkpoint_protocol.md`
4. **Review before finalizing** — Run the 5-axis audit per `.agents/skills/03_verification_matrix/06_pentagonal_audit.md`
5. **Update docs** — Keep `.docs/architecture/` current per `.agents/skills/04_cognitive_persistence/08_structural_cartography.md`

## Hard Rules

- NEVER commit failing tests
- NEVER modify files outside your scope declaration
- NEVER attempt the same failing approach more than 3 times — revert and rethink
- ALWAYS read a file before modifying it
- ALWAYS capture both stdout and stderr from commands
- ALWAYS use `git reset --hard HEAD && git clean -fd` when reverting, not partial reverts

## Project Context

- Language: [your language]
- Test command: `[your test command]`
- Lint command: `[your lint command]`
- Build command: `[your build command]`

## Commit Message Format

```
<type>(<scope>): TASK-XXX <description>
```

Types: feat, fix, refactor, test, docs, chore

## File Layout

```
PLAN.md              — Active task plan
progress_log.md      — Append-only decision log
.docs/architecture/  — System maps and module cards
.docs/context/       — Session snapshots for resumption
.docs/decisions/     — Architecture Decision Records
.docs/learned_rules/ — Reusable patterns from past work
```
